programmes.show_description: Defense Attorney Nikki Staines finds herself as a victim of rape following a police charity event; a hesitant Benson turns to her own for a suspect.
DNA evidence in a murder case leads Danny and Baez to identical twins with identical alibis. Also, Frank learns Nicky is interviewing for a job at the Justice Coalition.
As Jamie and Eddie's wedding nears, Erin interviews a witness that makes her doubt Eddie's honesty. Danny and Baez unravel the complicated love life of a young man who was murdered.
A business owner flags down officers when an erratic man starts climbing on his car. Unusual circumstances allow officers to cut a driver some slack for being honest.

A daily round-up of showbiz news and gossip from around the world, focusing on celebrities, movies, music and entertainment.
Corporal Punishment: A marine suffering from post-traumatic stress disorder escapes from a secure naval medical centre and goes on a rampage.
Tribes: The murder of a Muslim Marine points towards a possible al-Qaeda terrorist cell operating on US soil.
Stakeout: US crime drama series. The agents are staking out a warehouse in connection with some stolen Navy radar equipment when they stumble upon a murder.
Powerful American drama about the investigation and prosecution of crime. A conman is accused of brutally murdering three adults and a child.
Whose Monkey Is It Anyway?: When a monkey kills a lab worker, the man who freed the primates is charged with murder.
Sunday In The Park With Jorge: Powerful American drama series about lawyers and police. A day of celebrations in Central Park ends in murder when a wealthy woman is found dead.
Deep Vote: A murder victim who was killed in a case of mistaken identity is linked to the recent election of a state senator.
Who Let The Dogs Out: Crime drama. Detectives are called to the scene of a fatal attack on a woman by a pit-bull and must track down the dog and its owner before someone else is hurt.
A shoe-shine man is stabbed to death. Was the victim the Vietnam war hero he claimed to be?
Murder 2.0: A serial killer who posts footage of his crimes online engages Gibbs and the team in a murderous game of cat and mouse.
Collateral Damage: A robbery at Quantico base leaves a guard dead. As the agents investigate, they realise that cash may not have been the robbers' objective.
Cloak: Gibbs sets his team the task of infiltrating a secure navy facility to steal a classified military file.
Riley's personal and professional lives clash when his brother is connected to a murder investigation; Price takes a chance on a witness who can testify to a hidden motive.
Crime drama series. The SVU joins forces with an undercover taskforce to take down a human trafficking ring.
Rollins sets out undercover to pursue a suspect who administers drugs to tourists and assaults them, while Benson helps the victims resolve their memories.
Crime drama series. The team investigates a case where a woman accuses her therapist of sexual assault.
Crime drama series. The team investigates a pregnant teenager who refuses to divulge information about the father of the child.
Reese and Fusco become caught up in the gang war between Elias and Dominic as it reaches crisis point. Finch and Root follow a clue to Shaw's whereabouts.
Finch and Root race to save The Machine, which has been located by the rival AI, Samaritan.
A suspect on the run makes a dangerous decision when he finds himself cornered. An unsuspecting driver gets more than she bargained for when she gives an old friend a lift.

A daily round-up of showbiz news and gossip from around the world, focusing on celebrities, movies, music and entertainment.
Dog Tags: The lead suspect in a Navy drug-smuggling investigation turns up dead, apparently mauled by his own dog. But Abby is sure that the dog is innocent.
Internal Affairs: The NCIS agents are investigated by the FBI on suspicion of murdering an arms dealer known as La Grenouille.
In the Zone: The murder of a marine captain in Baghdad leads to a murky property deal back in the US. Tony and Nikki head to Iraq to investigate.
Teenage Wasteland: The owner of a Chinese restaurant is brutally murdered on a delivery and the suspects are a pack of teenagers.
Phobia: A gay man is beaten to death and his sick baby is stolen from him, forcing the police into a desperate search for the baby's kidnappers.
A Losing Season: Powerful American crime series. A pregnant woman is found shot in the trunk of a car and the trail leads to drugs and a basketball star.
A murder which appears to be mob-related proves more complicated than first thought.
A double homicide is linked to blood diamonds used to fund the Sierra Leonean civil war.
The sole remaining resident of an upper West Side apartment building is found murdered.
Dagger: Gibbs forms an uneasy alliance with Agent Lee in order to catch the man who has kidnapped her daughter.
Road Kill: US crime drama series. The suspicious death of a petty officer leads the agents to an underground street-fighting organisation and a zealous neighbourhood-watch group.
Silent Night: US crime drama series. A former petty officer thought to have been dead for 17 years is implicated in a double homicide.
Following a series of fatal shootings, the BAU team travels to Illinois to investigate what appears to be a copycat serial killer.
A fellow detective asks the SVU for help when he suspects his two daughters are being groomed by a serial predator; Kat disobeys the captain's orders.
A desperate father decides to take matters into his own hands in the case against his daughter's attacker.
Crime drama series. Benson helps an exchange student who is traumatised after a cab driver assaulted her.
